Governor Hope Uzodinma of Imo State has ordered security agents to fish out those behind the recent clashes in Okigwe, which left three death and scores wounded. The order came as relative calm had returned to Okigwe after rival cult gangs clashed resulting in free for all. Speaking while on a visit to the area, the governor assured Okigwe people that government was on top of the situation and urged them to go about their normal businesses without any fear. Uzodinma said that he had instructed security agencies to provide adequate protection for the town.  Imo APC crisis: We have no governorship candidate yet – Ekechi How we will work with Uzodinma — Imo PDP lawmakers Leadership change looms as Imo lawmakers resume today